{
  "doc_id": "55222",
  "text": "The scarcity of salivary gland tumors with intracranial metastases makes clinical trials of chemotherapy difficult. Several agents have shown benefit in non-randomized studies, with carboplatin and paclitaxel being the most frequently used. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Also, trastuzumab has been shown to have low activity levels in HER2/Neu overexpressing salivary gland tumors in a phase II study. [CITATION_3] Small molecules targeting cancers with distinct molecular profiles, such as the case in Patient 3, are currently being evaluated (ClinicalTrials. gov identifier: NCT01390818).",
